D. GALKOVSKY: "Democracy is a more ANCIENT (and more PRIMITIVE) [in the evolutionary sense of lower primates, apes, etc.] form of government. Monarchy arises only at a very high level of social specialization and is formed by the gradual suppression of democratic institutions."

From the viewpoint of governing, the monarchical form is far more effective. But monarchy is extremely fragile. The culmination of this struggle [with "re-emerging" crude democracy] is the periodic emergence and equally periodic annihilation of tyrants (e.g. impostors, usurpers).
